      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SANTINO KADE (5) goes very well at the distance with seven wins and a placing from 13 starts. Was out of placings last time (23.13) at Wagga in a Grade 4/5, finishing fourth and beaten 6 lengths. Rates on top and should go close. GO FORWARD BLOCK (1) could not have been more impressive last start in his speedy 24.92 win at Gunnedah in a Grade 4/5 over 431m. Expected to feature again. LITTLE KING (2) has a fair record and proved too classy last time to win by a nose at Temora in a handy 18.94 beating Time For Tea. The form from his last run is stacking up nicely. Will go close again if runs up to latest. LONG DARK ROAD (3) can improve on an unplaced run here last time out.",
